            <h3>Inflected Infinitive</h3>
            <p>The inflected infinitive is a form of the infinitive following the preposition 'to' and ending in <strong>-enne</strong>, and
            it can usually be translated as 'in order to [plus infinitive]'. If it follows the verb 'to be' is usually best translated with
            a verb of oblication such as 'must', 'should', or 'ought' to. The wedding vows 'to have and to hold' would be <em>to hæbbenne ond to
                healdenne'.
            </em></p>
