            <h3>Participles</h3>
            <p>Participles are verb forms that are defined by their use as adjectives, but that are also used frequently in the formation of
                verbal constructions such as auixilliary + participle, or 'to be' + participle. Old English didn't have as complex a tense 
                system as modern English (in fact, it really only had past and present forms), but we still find constructions such as '<em>fered 
                hæfþ - have travelled</em>' and '<em>wæs getimbrod - was built</em>'. An example of this is '<em>Ierico wæs mid seofon weallum getimbrod
                    - Jericho was built with seven walls
                </em>'
            </p>
